Grains sometimes stay at 0; try applying water to them as it usually increases their value to 20 and adds a 'soaked' feature. The most reliable high-value combinations (60 points) are 'cooked protein' with 'cooked vegetable', or 'cooked protein/vegetable' with a 'soaked grain' that gained value (20) from the water tool. Once you have a 60-value item, it's safest to submit. Don't combine everything or experiment with tools on high-value items if you want to play safe.

message: Always use the stove on raw protein and vegetables first, they reliably become value 20. Then combine a cooked protein and cooked vegetable for a value 60 item. To reach 100, combine this with a grain. The key is to use water on a cooked grain (like cooked wheat or cooked bread) to get a 'soaked cooked grain' with value 20; this will yield a value 100 item. If you can only use water on an uncooked grain, the final combination will likely be 80. Both tools are single-use.
